{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JFkRRo6fd7WCE7xZR8iApU","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have a comprehensive picture. Let me create a summary document for you:\n\n## Backend Test Setup Summary\n\nI've thoroughly explored the backend test infrastructure at `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`. Here's what I found:\n\n### Vitest Configuration\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/vitest.config.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { defineConfig } from \"vitest/config\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    environment: \"node\",\n    // DB-backed tests share a single Postgres database; run files sequentially\n    // to avoid TRUNCATE races between beforeEach hooks.\n    fileParallelism: false,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**Key Point**: Tests run sequentially (`fileParallelism: false`) because they share a single Postgres database. This prevents race conditions during `TRUNCATE` operations in `beforeEach` hooks.\n\n### Package.json Test Configuration\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/package.json`\n\n- **Test script**: `\"test\": \"vitest --passWithNoTests\"`\n- **Dev dependencies**: vitest ^2.1.0\n- **Runtime DB**: postgres ^3.4.0\n- **Auth/security**: jose ^6.0.0 (JWT), tweetnacl ^1.0.3 (EdDSA signatures)\n- **Blockchain**: @solana/web3.js ^1.98.0, @coral-xyz/anchor ^0.32.1\n\n### Existing Test Files\n\n#### 1. **auth.test.ts** — JWT Middleware Tests\nTests the `createJwtAuthMiddleware` with:\n- Valid JWT acceptance and context setting\n- Missing/malformed Authorization header rejection\n- Expired JWT rejection\n- Wrong secret rejection\n- GET requests pass without auth\n- Wallet extracted from JWT `sub` claim\n\n#### 2. **fairness.test.ts** — Fairness Utilities Tests\nTests core fairness functions:\n- `generateSecret()` — 32-byte buffer generation, uniqueness\n- `computeCommitment()` — SHA256(secret), determinism, matches packages/fairness algorithm\n- `generateMatchId()` — 8-byte random ID generation\n- `deriveMatchPda()` — PDA derivation with seeds `[\"match\", creator, matchId]`, determinism, uniqueness per creator\n\n#### 3. **rate-limit.test.ts** — Rate Limiting Middleware Tests\nTests the `createRateLimitMiddleware` with:\n- Per-wallet rate limiting (tracks independently)\n- Global rate limiting across all wallets\n- `Retry-After` header on 429 responses\n- GET requests are not rate-limited\n- Window-based expiry\n\n#### 4. **endpoints.test.ts** — Full HTTP Endpoint Tests (600+ lines)\nExercises the full middleware stack (auth + rate limit) with:\n\n**POST /fairness/coinflip/create**:\n- 200 with valid JWT\n- 401 without JWT / expired JWT\n- 403 when body wallet mismatches JWT wallet\n- 409 on duplicate PDA (collision detection)\n- 429 when rate limit exceeded\n- Response includes: `transaction`, `matchPda`, `commitment` (64 hex chars), `lastValidBlockHeight`\n\n**POST /fairness/lord/create**:\n- 200 with valid JWT\n- Response includes: `transaction`, `roundPda`, `matchId`, `commitment`, `lastValidBlockHeight`\n\n**GET /fairness/rounds/:pda**:\n- 200 for known PDA with full round data\n- 404 for unknown PDA\n- Unsettled rounds omit `secret` and `verification` fields\n- Returns: `pda`, `game`, `phase`, `creator`, `commitment`, `amountLamports`, `side`, `createdAt`, `updatedAt`\n\n**GET /health**:\n- 200 with fields: `status`, `version`, `serverKey`, `solBalance`, `dbConnected`, `workerRunning`, `unsettledCount`, `oldestUnsettledAge`\n- Reflects unsettled round count\n\n#### 5. **integration.test.ts** — Full Lifecycle E2E Tests (550+ lines)\nComplete create → join → settle → verify flow with:\n\n**Mock Connection Features**:\n- In-memory account storage with `setAccount()`, `removeAccount()`\n- `getAccountInfo()`, `getProgramAccounts()` with memcmp/dataSize filters\n- `sendRawTransaction()`, `confirmTransaction()`, `getSlot()`\n- Slot manipulation for testing settlement triggers\n\n**Test Scenarios**:\n- Full lifecycle: create → join (mock) → settle → verify\n- DB state verification at each phase transition\n- Operator event audit trail (`secret_generated` → `match_detected` → `settle_submitted` → `settle_confirmed`)\n- Unsettled rounds don't expose secrets\n- Multiple creates from same wallet succeed (different match IDs)\n\n**Key Patterns**:\n- Uses `encodeCoinflipMatch()` and `encodeCoinflipConfig()` to build mock account data\n- Triggers settlement worker with `worker.poll()`\n- Uses `retrySettler.attemptSettle(pda)` for settlement execution\n- Verifies DB phases and operator events\n\n#### 6. **auth-routes.test.ts** — Challenge-Response Auth Flow Tests (300+ lines)\nFull authentication lifecycle:\n\n**Challenge → Verify → Refresh → Logout**:\n- POST /auth/challenge: returns `nonce` (64 hex chars), `message`, `expiresAt`\n- POST /auth/verify: validates Ed25519 signature, returns `accessToken`, `refreshToken`\n- POST /auth/refresh: rotates refresh tokens, blocks token reuse\n- POST /auth/logout: revokes refresh token (204 No Content)\n\n**Edge Cases**:\n- Rejects challenge with missing wallet\n- Rejects verify with wrong wallet\n- Rejects verify with wrong signature\n- Rejects nonce reuse\n- Rejects invalid refresh tokens after logout\n\n### Database Connection Setup\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`\n\n- Uses `postgres` npm package (not node-postgres)\n- All tests hardcode: `postgresql://vscode@localhost:5432/rng_utopia_dev`\n- `beforeAll`: Creates connection with `createDb(DATABASE_URL)`\n- `beforeEach`: Truncates tables with `TRUNCATE rounds, operator_events RESTART IDENTITY`\n- `afterAll`: Closes with `db.close()` and `sql.end()`\n\n### Database Schema Configuration\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts`\n\n- Supports custom schema via `DB_SCHEMA` env var (defaults to `public`)\n- Applies `-csearch_path` option to connection URL for non-default schemas\n\n### Test Helper Patterns\n\n1. **JWT Creation**: Uses `jose` SignJWT with HS256\n   ```typescript\n   const token = await new SignJWT({ sub: wallet })\n     .setProtectedHeader({ alg: \"HS256\" })\n     .setIssuedAt(now)\n     .setExpirationTime(now + expiresIn)\n     .sign(secret);\n   ```\n\n2. **Keypair Generation**: Uses `@solana/web3.js` Keypair\n3. **HTTP Testing**: Uses Hono's `.request()` method (not fetch)\n4. **DB Isolation**: Sequential file execution + per-test TRUNCATE\n5. **Mock Accounts**: Custom `MockConnection` class with in-memory account storage\n\n### File Locations\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/vitest.config.ts` | Vitest root config |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/auth.test.ts` | JWT auth middleware |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/fairness.test.ts` | Fairness utilities (secrets, PDAs) |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts` | Rate limiting |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` | Full endpoint stack tests |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` | E2E lifecycle tests |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts` | Auth flow tests |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts` | DB client factory |\n| `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db-config.ts` | Schema configuration |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af04eba9eb80ceb21 (use SendMessage with to: 'af04eba9eb80ceb21' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 69108\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 66631</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5a06e2aa-bee3-40eb-a97d-65518436146f","uuid":"7dc71d56-6208-425a-